# cms/.gitignore — gitignore rules for the CMS content-production
# sub-tree. Anything that's specifically about the content runtime /
# CMS pipeline state lives here; cross-project concerns (Python
# __pycache__, IDE dirs, OS junk, secrets, ...) stay in the root
# .gitignore so they apply uniformly.

# CMS-host secrets now live in GitHub Environments. Operators fetch them
# into the process env via `eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-cms)"`
# before running cms/run.sh or cms/scripts/staging.sh. There is no longer
# a local cms/.env file to gitignore.
#
# (历史: 之前这里是 .env, 由 cms/scripts/env.sh 引导创建并用 gitignored
#  cms/.env.example.cms 当模板。现在两文件都已删除, env.sh 也退役。)

# .local/ — CMS working dir (per-machine state). Currently only
# holds audio/ (local MP3 cache for CLOUD_PROVIDER=local_fs fallback);
# may grow per-machine state in the future (caches, logs, ...). Lives
# inside the project so default-path writes work on Windows + sandboxed
# Linux hosts without extra setup. dev/prod runtime does NOT read this
# — audio is uploaded to Tencent Cloud COS by generate_audio.py, and
# the staging dir (the CMS pipeline output) lives at ./staging/ (sibling
# of .gitignore) which is git-tracked and NOT under .local/, so this
# rule does not affect it.
.local/
.local/**